description: Diddy Kong Racing is a kart racing game with a story mode, complete with bosses and hidden collectibles.

v0.1.0.description:
Initial release of the Diddy Kong Racing Archipelago integration.

Features:
- Shuffle golden balloons and keys, optionally shuffle Wizpig and T.T. amulet pieces.
- Option to start with all 1st place trophies.
- Two options for victory condition, winning either the first or second Wizpig race.
- Press D-pad up to print what regional golden balloons and keys you currently have in the Lua console.

Known Quirks:
- If you find all 8 regional balloons for a region before winning first boss race of that region, you will skip to the second boss race (this is to avoid a glitch).
- If you beat the first boss race in a region before completing all the race 1's for that region, after completing a race 1, if you don't have enough balloons to enter race 2, you will be stuck inside the locked door. To get around this, you can go back into the race, pause, and return to lobby.
- Collected keys reappear when reloading a race.

Special Thanks:
- [jjjj12212](https://github.com/jjjj12212) and everyone who has contributed to the [Banjo-Tooie Archipelago integration](https://github.com/jjjj12212/Archipelago-BanjoTooie). This project is based off of their work. Not only was having their example to work off of hugely helpful, I had never even heard of RAM hacking before playing Banjo-Tooie in Archipelago, so I would never been able to do this without them.
- [David Benepe](https://github.com/DavidSM64) and everyone who has contributed to the in-progress [Diddy Kong Racing decompilation](https://github.com/DavidSM64/Diddy-Kong-Racing). Referencing that helped a lot with RAM searching.
v0.1.0.title: v0.1.0

v0.2.0.description:
Changes:
- Added options to start with balloons, regional balloons, wizpig amulet pieces and T.T. amulet pieces
- Mark keys and T.T. amulet pieces as filler depending on settings

Game details page: https://github.com/zakwiz/DiddyKongRacingAP/blob/main/worlds/diddy_kong_racing/docs/en_Diddy_Kong_Racing.md
Setup guide: https://github.com/zakwiz/DiddyKongRacingAP/blob/main/worlds/diddy_kong_racing/docs/setup_en.md
v0.2.0.title: v0.2.0

v0.2.1.description:
### Improvements

- You can now run the Lua script at any point in the game, leave it connected when resetting, etc., as it now detects when you are in a save file.

Game details page: https://github.com/zakwiz/DiddyKongRacingAP/blob/main/worlds/diddy_kong_racing/docs/en_Diddy_Kong_Racing.md
Setup guide: https://github.com/zakwiz/DiddyKongRacingAP/blob/main/worlds/diddy_kong_racing/docs/setup_en.md
v0.2.1.title: v0.2.1

v0.2.2.description:
No notable user-facing changes with this release, but it adds some settings to the slot data to facilitate future auto-tracker work.

### Changes

- Per best practices, keys are no longer ever marked as filler, as they always unlock a new check, even if that check is known to be filler.
v0.2.2.title: v0.2.2

v0.2.3.description:
### Fixes
- Victory condition will no longer trigger prematurely if the condition has been cleared on an existing save file
v0.2.3.title: v0.2.3

v0.2.4.description:
### Changes
- Pausing will set all item counts based on the received item map, this will correct for any items that were received by the client but not successfully added to the save file

### Fixes
- This apworld should now work on WIndows 7, as it is now compatible with Python 3.8
v0.2.4.title: v0.2.4

v0.2.5.description:
### Fixes
- In-game regional balloon counts are capped at 8 to prevent an issue where it was impossible to do the 2nd boss race
v0.2.5.title: v0.2.5

v0.2.6.description:
### Fixes
- Corrected Future Fun Land access logic
v0.2.6.title: v0.2.6

v0.3.0.description:
### Changes
- Added option to shuffle balloon door requirements. Universal Tracker is highly recommended if enabling this option in order to see what races are available: https://github.com/FarisTheAncient/Archipelago/releases/tag/Tracker_v0.1.11

### Known Quirks
- If you complete a race 1 after beating its boss 1, but before unlocking its race 2, you will be stuck in the door upon exiting and will have to quit the save file and reload. I will look into ways to fix this in a future release.
v0.3.0.title: v0.3.0

v0.3.1.description:
### Fixes
- Prevent Lua from crashing when the shuffle_door_requirements option is turned off
v0.3.1.title: v0.3.1

v0.4.0.description:
### Changes
- Added options to customize balloon door requirement progression
  - In addition to vanilla, you can now choose a linear or exponential progression, and pick what the maximum requirement will be (this doesn't affect the Wizpig 2 door)
- Pressing right on the D-pad will print what doors are open and uncompleted in the Lua console if door requirements are non-vanilla
- Client now prints an error if the local apworld version is different than the apworld used in generation
- Lua script now prints an error if run on a BizHawk version other than 2.9.1
v0.4.0.title: v0.4.0

v0.5.0.description:
### Changes
- New setting: open worlds. If enabled, all worlds, including Future Fun Land, will be open from the start
- Removed settings for starting items, as the same result can be achieved using starting inventory
- Client can now be run directly from the command line
- BizHawk will save RAM changes to disk when receiving an item, hopefully preventing data loss on crash

### Fixes
- Keys are now only in logic with access to the relevant silver coin challenge to prevent softlocks
- Maximum door requirement can now be set without shuffling door requirements
v0.5.0.title: v0.5.0

v0.5.1.description:
### Fixes
- Removes world unlock locations when the `open_worlds` setting is set to `true`, preventing unfilled locations causing generation errors
v0.5.1.title: v0.5.1

v0.5.2.description:
### Fixed
- Snowball Valley door is no longer permanently stuck closed when using the following settings together:
  - `open_worlds` = `true`
  - `shuffle_door_requirements` = `false`
  - `door_requirement_progression` = `vanilla`
v0.5.2.title: v0.5.2

v0.6.0.description:
### New
- Added options to reduce the requirements for unlocking boss and Wizpig races
- Drumstick and T.T. are always unlocked
- Added support for map tracking in PopTracker

### Changed
- Bizhawk version 2.10 is now required

### Fixed
- If the connector Lua is run on an incorrect ROM, an appropriate error message will be printed and no items will be sent
- In-game item counts should have less problems desyncing from Archipelago item counts

### Special thanks
- Ozone for making the PopTracker
- Pokemongenius for help with RAM searching
v0.6.0.title: v0.6.0

v0.6.1.description:
### Changes
- Drumstick and T.T. will be unlocked on the title screen instead of after selecting a save file
- A user-friendly error will print in the Lua console if the Lua connector is run from outside the data/lua folder
v0.6.1.title: v0.6.1

v1.0.0.description:
Huge thanks to [jjjj12212](https://github.com/jjjj12212) for creating the ROM patch and lots of additional help, making all these changes possible!

### New
- The client will now patch your vanilla ROM once per version, and you will need to use the patched ROM for the randomizer. The ROM is still not required for generation. More detailed instructions can be found [here](https://github.com/zakwiz/DiddyKongRacingAP/blob/main/worlds/diddy_kong_racing/docs/setup_en.md#how-to-install---client-side).
- Door requirements are displayed correctly in-game when door requirements are not vanilla
- Option to randomly change your character every time you switch maps
- Option to shuffle power-up balloons between all possible power-ups (doesn't affect bosses, Icicle Pyramid, and Darkwater Beach)
- An in-game dialog will display when you find or receive items for your own slot
- The intro cutscene is skipped

### Changed
- .agi files are no longer used
v1.0.0.title: v1.0.0

v1.1.0.description:
Huge thanks to [jjjj12212](https://github.com/jjjj12212) for creating the ROM patch and lots of additional help, making all these changes possible!

### New
- Added option to shuffle track entrances
- Added option to use mirrored tracks
- Added option to randomize track music
- Added deferred entrances support for Universal Tracker for when track entrances are shuffled
- Added option groups
- Added item groups

### Changed
- The connector Lua now accepts any Bizhawk version 2.10 or newer
- Improved how door unlock requirements are shown in the spoiler log
- Updated and clarified Lua error messages

### Fixed
- Future Fun Land locations are now properly randomized when the goal is Wizpig 1 but the open worlds setting is enabled
- Door requirements are now properly shuffled when the shuffle door requirements setting is enabled but door requirement progression is vanilla
v1.1.0.title: v1.1.0

v1.1.1.description:
Huge thanks to [jjjj12212](https://github.com/jjjj12212) for creating the ROM patch and lots of additional help, making all these changes possible!

### New
- The power-up balloon next to the bell in Boulder Canyon will always be blue, ignoring the `power_up_balloon_type` option
- Added manifest for APv0.7.0 compatibility

### Changed
- Change the `mirrored_tracks` option to `track_version` to reflect that the option does more than just mirror the tracks

### Fixed
- Universal tracker now works with the `shuffle_race_entrances` option
- Player vehicle is now always correct in Icicle Pyramid and Darkwater Beach
- Trophy races now always unlocks after beating boss 2
- Player vehicle is now always correct in trophy races
- Silver coin races now work when a non-Future Fun Land track is behind a Future Fun Land door
- Restarting a silver coin race from the pause menu no longer changes the race to a pre-silver coin race
v1.1.1.title: v1.1.1

v1.1.2.description:
### Fixed
- Having multiple Diddy Kong Racing slots in the same multiworld will no longer cause all slots to have the same randomization of track versions, music, entrances, and door requirements, ignoring logic

Huge thanks to [jjjj12212](https://github.com/jjjj12212) for creating the ROM patch and lots of additional help.
v1.1.2.title: v1.1.2

v1.1.3.description:
### Fixed
- Combining a non-vanilla door requirement progression with unshuffled door requirements no longer uses vanilla door requirement progression
- Added missing DF Balloon item group
v1.1.3.title: v1.1.3
